			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Note this is for x86-32 and x86-64 only, not ARM.  On ARM we are using a new instruction sequence for calls that avoids the need to place the bl/blx instruction at the end of a bundle, but does not change the function calling convention at all.  (Doing the equivalent for x86 is prohibitively costly in the call sequence.)

This should probably have separate subordinate issues for the pieces of the puzzle, which will be implemented at different times and perhaps by different people.
1. syscall return changes (http://codereview.chromium.org/10700017/)
2. validator changes
